Mercury General Corp., the Los
Angeles-based auto insurer, said Nathan Bessin will retire from
the board of directors at the end of the year.  Bessin, 85, has been a director of the company for 20 years
and is a member of the Nominating/Corporate Governance
Committee, the insurer said today in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
